PathMNIST MLLO Revision 


# Proposed Classes

| New Class | Reason |
|-----------|--------|
| BatchNormalizationLayer | Represents BatchNorm2d layers |
| SGDOptimizer | Represents stochastic gradient descent |
| CrossEntropyLoss | Represents CrossEntropyLoss |
| LearningRate | Represents learning-rate hyperparameters |
| Momentum | Represents optimizer momentum |
| AreaUnderROCCurve | Represents AUC evaluation metrics |
| PyTorch | Represents the PyTorch framework |
| DataLoadingOperation | Represents dataset loading |
| DataBatchingOperation | Represents batching operations |
| FromScratchModel | Distinguishes custom-trained models |

---

# Proposed Object Properties

| Property | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| usesFramework | Training → framework |
| usesLossFunction | Training → loss |
| hasEvaluationMetric | Evaluation → metrics |
| hasEpoch | Training → epochs |
| hasModelProvenance | Model → pretrained/custom |

---
# PathMNIST Re-encoding Comparison

| Original Encoding | Revised Encoding |
|-------------------|-----------------|
| OptimizationAlgorithm | SGDOptimizer |
| LossFunction | CrossEntropyLoss |
| DataProcessingOperation | DataLoadingOperation |
| No BatchNorm representation | Five BatchNormalizationLayer individuals |
| No AUC | AreaUnderROCCurve individuals |
| No LearningRate | LearningRate individual |
| No Momentum | Momentum individual |
| No PyTorch | PyTorch framework individual |
| No batching operation | DataBatchingOperation |
| No model provenance | FromScratchModel |

---

## Overall Improvement

The revised encoding captures more information from the original implementation while reducing reliance on generic classes.

Most previously identified ontology gaps are now represented using dedicated ontology classes and properties.
